The paper discusses a learning algorithm for robotic manipulation of deformable tissues in surgical interventions, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses Q-learning, which is a popular reinforcement learning technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The simulation involves image processing using OpenCV library (cs.CV). The algorithm involves human knowledge in selecting features, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the algorithm in surgical robotics, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
